      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing the law to ensure equal treatment is a core tenet of many secular frameworks. Strictly enforcing mandates for all citizens arguably upholds the principle of state neutrality. Nonetheless, if the state's mandate forces an undue burden on deeply held religious convictions, the argument for freedom of religion gains significant weight. The tension remains between universal application of the law and the protection of fundamental individual liberties.",
      "source": "target",
